      <h2 class="section-heading">The Gnostic Key</h2>

      <p class="lead muted">
        <strong>The Gnostic Key</strong> is a living digital library, part sacred archive and part social experiment, created to preserve wisdom, expose power, and reawaken collective sovereignty.
      </p>

      <p>
        Founded in the United Kingdom and published by <em>The Gnostic Key Limited</em>, the project unites research, symbolism, investigative journalism, and metaphysical study within one coherent system.
        Each pillar of TGK, from <a href="/pillars/the-teachings/"><strong>The Teachings</strong></a> to <a href="/pillars/the-obsidian-key/"><strong>The Obsidian Key</strong></a>, is designed to illuminate a distinct aspect of truth: spiritual, political, historical, or systemic.
      </p>

      <h3 class="section-subheading">Purpose and Vision</h3>
      <p>
        TGK exists to restore depth to public understanding in an age of distraction and deception.
        Its mission is to teach discernment, moral courage, and intellectual independence, the essential qualities of the true seeker.
        Through its episodes, archives, and symbolic systems, TGK seeks to unveil the architecture of control and the hidden laws that shape modern life.
      </p>

      <h3 class="section-subheading">Structure and Sovereignty</h3>
      <p>
        The Gnostic Key operates as an independent knowledge commons under <strong>The Gnostic Key Limited</strong>, a UK registered entity committed to transparency, fair use, and public accountability.
        The platform is self funded through reader membership and symbolic commerce, ensuring complete freedom from institutional or corporate influence.
      </p>

      <p>
        All paid content tiers directly support research, preservation, and the creation of new public archives.
        TGK does not sell user data and hosts no advertising or sponsored material.
      </p>

